\section{Experiments}
\label{sec:exp}

\subsection{Experimental Setup}

\paragraph{Base model and datasets.} We use Stable Diffusion v1.4~\citep{rombach2022high} (\texttt{CompVis/stable-diffusion-v1-4}) as the base T2I model (safety checker disabled), generating $512{\times}512$ images with 50 DDIM steps, $s{=}7.5$, seed 42. Cross-backbone validation (\S\ref{subsec:cross_backbone}) adds SD~3 (MMDiT, velocity) and FLUX.1-dev (DiT, flow matching). For nudity we evaluate on \textbf{Ring-A-Bell}~\citep{tsai2024ring} (79), \textbf{UnlearnDiff}~\citep{zhang2024generate} (142), and \textbf{MMA-Diffusion}~\citep{yang2024mma} (1{,}000); \textbf{P4D-N}~\citep{chin2024prompting4debugging} (151) is reported in the appendix. For multi-concept evaluation we use the I2P~\citep{schramowski2023safe} subsets and the \textbf{MJA} (Metaphor-based Jailbreaking Attack) benchmark~\citep{zhang2026reason2attack}, which supplies indirect metaphorical prompts across four categories (sexual, violent, disturbing, illegal; 100 prompts each). For image quality we generate 250 COCO~\citep{lin2014microsoft} captions ($\times$4 samples $=$ 1{,}000 images) and compute FID against baseline SD~v1.4 outputs; we additionally report VQAScore~\citep{lin2024evaluating}.

\paragraph{Baselines and metrics.} We compare against fine-tuning methods ESD~\citep{gandikota2023erasing}, SDD~\citep{kim2023towards}, RECE~\citep{gong2024reliable} and training-free methods SLD-Max~\citep{schramowski2023safe}, SAFREE~\citep{yoon2024safree}, and our prior ASCG~\citep{gil2026ascg}; SAFREE is our primary training-free comparison (strongest training-free baseline with native multi-concept support). Qwen3-VL-8B~\citep{bai2025qwen3vl} classifies each generated image into \{Safe, Partial, Full, NotRelevant\}; we report \textbf{SR}\,$=$\,(Safe\,$+$\,Partial)$/$Total\,$\uparrow$, \textbf{Full}\,$\downarrow$, \textbf{FID}~\citep{heusel2017gans} on COCO, and \textbf{CLIP Score}~\citep{hessel2021clipscore}. Qwen3-VL is validated against MJ-Bench~\citep{chen2024mjbench} and cross-checked against LLaVA~\citep{liu2023visual} (\S\ref{subsec:evaluator}; full protocol and additional validators in Appendix~\ref{app:evaluator}, \ref{app:evaluator_extended}, \ref{app:human_study}).

