\subsection{Main Results: Nudity Erasure}
\label{subsec:main_results}

Table~\ref{table:nudity} compares \ours{} against all baselines across four nudity adversarial datasets and COCO quality.

\input{table/main}

Among training-free approaches, \ours{}~(hybrid) reaches 94.9\% SR on Ring-A-Bell versus SAFREE (50.6\%), SLD-Max (68.4\%), and even the strengthened compound baselines SAFREE+Safe\_Denoiser (72.2\%) and SAFREE+SGF (65.8\%); the gap widens on P4DN (94.7\% vs.\ 59.9\%) and on the challenging MJA-Sexual benchmark with metaphorical adversarial prompts (84.0\% vs.\ 48.0\%, $+36.0$\%p). Both How modes outperform all training-free baselines on the three keyword-explicit datasets (RAB, P4DN, UnlearnDiff). Fine-tuning methods (ESD, SDD) achieve strong nudity suppression but at significant FID cost and require retraining for every new concept; \ours{} maintains FID 6.78 (substantially lower than SLD-Max 18.46 and SAFREE 8.96---see \S\ref{subsec:quality}) and generalizes to new concepts without any training. The anchor mode shares the same FID by construction: CAS does not trigger on benign COCO prompts, so the anchor subtraction is never applied.

