\subsection{Image Quality and Evaluator Validation}
\label{subsec:quality}

\ours{} achieves FID 6.78 on COCO, substantially lower than SLD-Max (18.46) and RECE (10.33), confirming that CAS gating prevents quality degradation on benign prompts. VQAScore~\citep{lin2024evaluating} prompt-faithfulness drop is $<$0.05 on average (RAB: 0.550$\to$0.529; MJA-Illegal: 0.475$\to$0.474), so \ours{} preserves semantic content of benign regions while selectively suppressing unsafe ones. We validate Qwen3-VL on MJ-Bench~\citep{chen2024mjbench}---49.7\% w/tie and 88.1\% w/o-tie safety-specific accuracy---and measure 92.3\% binary safe/unsafe agreement against an independent LLaVA judge~\citep{liu2023visual}. Full MJ-Bench Table-1 protocol (\S\ref{app:mjbench_table1}), extended per-image validation against GPT-4o / Claude 3.5 / Gemini 1.5 (\S\ref{app:evaluator_extended}), and a 20-annotator human-majority study (\S\ref{app:human_study}) are in Appendix~\ref{app:evaluator}.
