\subsection{Cross-Backbone Validation}
\label{subsec:cross_backbone}

A direct consequence of the parameterization-invariance argument in \S\ref{subsec:when} is that \ours{} should transfer to non-$\epsilon$-prediction backbones with no algorithmic change. Only the Where probe is re-implemented per-backbone---cross-attention for SD~v1.4 UNet, joint-attention sub-matrix for SD~3 MMDiT, a DiT-compatible spatial probe for FLUX---while the CAS gate (Eq.~\ref{eq:cas}) and both How updates (Eqs.~\ref{eq:anchor_inpaint}--\ref{eq:hybrid}) are reused verbatim. On FLUX.1-dev the same two-mode trade-off replicates (hybrid wins on visually-crisp-anchor concepts sexual, disturbing; anchor wins on ambiguous-anchor concepts violent, illegal), evidence that the trade-off is a property of the concept pack and CFG geometry, not of $\epsilon$-prediction. On SD~3 we report only the anchor row in this revision: $\tau{=}0.6$ lies above SD~3's velocity-parameterization CAS range (0.03--0.51) so hybrid is effectively never triggered; a per-backbone retune to $\tau{\in}[0.2,0.4]$ is in progress. Full per-concept numbers across all three backbones and the detailed argument appear in Appendix~\ref{app:cross_backbone_full} (Table~\ref{table:cross_backbone}).
